4:
Whoa! A direct hit! Diletta's in
trouble now!
6:
Heh... Not bad... You've got the skills,
I'll give you that.
15:
Now THAT was a match! The crowd
was going bonkers!
23:
Haha, your eyes were practically
glued to the stage.
28:
Come on, you floating hunk o' junk!
Start up, dammit!
32: Huh? Wait, isn't that the fighter from—
46:
As an apology, feel free to eat as
much as you want! It's my treat!
49:
Oh, definitely grab a bit of that fish! I
just caught that bad boy this
morning!
53:
You did? Are you not a professional
fighter?
57:
Yeah, but I fish on the side. On a
backwater Float like this one, it's not
easy to get by just fighting—
60:
Wait, how'd you know I was a
fighter? Didja happen to watch my
last match?
63:
We received tickets to your show as
a bonus for an errand we
completed. We were all thoroughly
entertained.
66:
Aw man, you shoulda said
something sooner!
70:
You're a pretty tough fighter, you
know that?
75:
Indeed. I was surprised to see you
deliberately put yourself in the way
of your opponent's attacks.
82:
I stop my opponent's strongest
move in its tracks, and then I win!
Really gets the crowd going, you
know?
86:
Well, I can't argue with that, but...
aren't you worried about getting
hurt?
90:
Nah, I've got plenty of tricks up my
sleeve. Like redirecting the force of
the attack or weakening it with a
blow of my own.
93: Although, to be honest, recently, I've—
96:
U-um... You're Diletta, right? I'm a
huge fan of yours! Can I get an
autograph?!
100:
Oho, a fan, eh? I'm kinda off-duty
right now, but what the heck!
Gimme some paper!
103:
I love how dramatic your fighting
style is! Consider me a fan for life!
106:
You know, you remind me of a
fighter from back in the day. Ever
heard of Ardor the Masked? You're
both such great fighters!
113: I ain't nothing like my old man!
116:
What a buzzkill... Saying crap like
that.
121: So your father was also a fighter.
125:
Yeah, but a real dumb one. All he
cared about was getting the crowd
going.
129:
I mean, that sounds a lot like what
you're doing...
134: No way! I'm actually trying to win!
138:
But Pops... He cared more about
giving a flashy performance. The
actual outcome of the match didn't
matter to him...
140:
He eventually got hurt and had to
retire.
143:
I refuse to turn out like my old man.
Someday, I'm gonna be the
champion of some big-time arena!
148:
Or at least I hope so! I know I've got
a long way to go!
149:
Anyway, sorry about that. I made
things a bit awkward, didn't I?
154: Not at all. We'll be cheering you on.
160:
Ah, if you really wanna support me,
how about helping me out with my
training?
163:
I don't know if you're bounty hunters
or scavengers, but you guys look
seriously strong.
167:
Well... I guess you could call us
fighters in our own right.
171:
I knew it! You see, I'm in a bit of
slump lately, so I've been on the
lookout for new ways to train.
175:
I see... Well, the strength you seek
may be different from what we can
provide.
178:
Yeah, I know, but if it'll help me out,
even just a little, I wanna give it a try!
182:
Then shall we head to Starview
Village?
186:
Star what now? Never heard of it.
That a Float somewhere?
191:
Uh... It's something like our own base
of operations. You won't run out of
sparring partners there, that much I
can assure you.
196:
Seriously?! Then take me with you to
this Starry Villa or whatever!
201:
Just one more question then,
Diletta... Can you keep a secret?
205:
Ah, I getcha... No worries there. I'm a
lady of my word. Your business is
safe with me.
210:
Then welcome to Starview Village,
Diletta.
214: Thanks! I really owe you guys!
218:
Hey, Chef! Grab all the fish I caught
today! We're gonna have ourselves
a party!
